Wash off the engine and then watch the engine for a leak. The oil may be 
coming from further than you think. If it is a crack - worry not you might 
be able to fix it with JB Weld for many, many miles.

May be a pushrod tube. Mine leaked at the base once when I overfilled the 
engine...


